{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"87920bfd-4968-42fe-b029-006d9dc33f5b","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a bridge for .NET 9 and is no longer needed. Your project already has `EnableMSTestRunner`, which is all MTP requires.\n\nJust remove the obsolete property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01DSnZmoU2hgsAjuSvmsQDGv","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01TqQMWEjy3nPbrWVj4uRyqJ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-e43eaa4dd16041498f025b607f9bc7a1/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-e43eaa4dd16041498f025b607f9bc7a1/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"67d5b02a-ba46-42b8-94f2-411ca4e904f2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` has native support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed.\n\nLet me provide the correct guidance:\n\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform when it detects an MTP-compatible test project (like one with `EnableMSTestRunner`).\n2. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\n\n3. Since the project already has `EnableMSTestRunner`, it's already configured as an MTP project, so I can update the project file accordingly.","outputTokens":493,"requestId":"481E:99ACC:32159F6:36ADE65:69FBE38B"},"id":"c00749d3-dc8e-40e3-b6f1-e139d757bbc6","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:57:55.687Z","parentId":"c072ef65-b266-4e71-be7f-c58c3995d5f7"}
