{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2bcac96d-4154-4b42-9394-61d3750274f3","content":"**Summary:**\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — **remove it**. It was needed in .NET 9 to opt `dotnet test` into the MTP pipeline. In .NET 10, this is the default behavior.\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner`** — **keep it**. This tells MSTest to build your test project as an MTP executable, which is what `dotnet test` now expects.\n\nYour updated `.csproj` is ready. Just run `dotnet test` as usual — it will go through MTP natively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"67d5b02a-ba46-42b8-94f2-411ca4e904f2","outputTokens":136,"requestId":"481E:99ACC:3217964:36B0237:69FBE393"},"id":"ce9bf372-23c0-428a-b709-1d4cfab8e5e3","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:58:03.513Z","parentId":"277ec13b-2cc1-451e-834a-a263e7874ce9"}
